    {
      "event": "committed",
      "id": null,
      "node_id": "C_kwDOABII59oAKDU0NjU5OGI3MzY3NWJkNTY2M2RlNmRmOGY0ZTNhMjNhMGU3ZWNlYjc",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/546598b73675bd5663de6df8f4e3a23a0e7eceb7",
      "actor": null,
      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": null,
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/546598b73675bd5663de6df8f4e3a23a0e7eceb7",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "fd8fb0ccfee8d6d02864a9d42307170b6be8a836",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/fd8fb0ccfee8d6d02864a9d42307170b6be8a836"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree fd8fb0ccfee8d6d02864a9d42307170b6be8a836\nparent 0fb5e167e8e332e3d40659406b3222a22747aa0e\nauthor Cory Fields <cory-nospam-@coryfields.com> 1777399236 +0000\ncommitter fanquake <fanquake@gmail.com> 1777557977 +0100\n\nmulti_index: fix compilation failure with boost >= 1.91\n\nThis effectively reverts a3cb309e7c31853f272bffaa65fb6ab0a7cc4083 from PR #30194.\n\nThat PR reduced the multi_index type signatures as recommended upstream, but\nthis is no longer supported as of boost 1.91 because it is no longer necessary.\n1.91 drops support for the pre-c++11 work-arounds that bloated the type\nsignatures to begin with.\n\nThe upstream `BOOST_MULTI_INDEX_ENABLE_MPL_SUPPORT` define is meant to provide\ncompatibility with removed features, but it does not work for this case. Using\n`indexed_by` directly when defining the `multi_index` (as opposed to inheriting\nfrom it) works with all versions, and avoids the use of the back-compat define.\n\nThis is a slight regression when building against boost < 1.91 because the\nbloated type signatures are reintroduced in that case, but it's not significant\nenough to go to the trouble of introducing version detection and ifdefs.\n\nGithub-Pull: #35175\nRebased-From: 0bc9d354dfd8074d1c36a891a69b6585a8775c65\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQJPBAABCAA5FiEEz7FuIclQ9n+pXlWPLuufXMCVJsEFAmnzYdsbFIAAAAAABAAO\nbWFudTIsMi41KzEuMTIsMCwzAAoJEC7rn1zAlSbBfFQP+gJNE8dzxrX12rspgSPy\n+qvP+3VWAjiTzDTjth5MdUxEdOQtuxU+PpfUjoRNKqsFL/vS/66hEmFgsxn/0twf\n+Z26UB/BSG0pX/W+j4CLE6fgOMjDXjgbB95DV0FZHnlLwldytCCApISnZ5nsKoPv\nUJfiGe3U/67TVKHQYb5+ILXEuttK6PJQL6cBnQxotROKlODYHPbeyZGPqmQ4OrZB\nekMx270tdNOHcSavGkkvreYH7eHZqJa6BcQ6FyMpyIRbh43h7SDPbtVpaEgMSPnb\nJk4MS82EKrU/yvomwGPQiLqHR2ak7RTlnJ1r8UmGB1j7u8BuNKEuF/Wl1PTHIRUW\n8taNrVjnZOY5moKDJ7MEjvOQZvoKxcULoPlYUjqVzteMpNnrUCl4YRObCn/7T61+\nr6RDe6Sa9dvLNbyYFYara8b8XrkqJ43BZp9Oa6ilp9QEFx0hvCrgCiz2aIy7o6eX\nEaI4vJfh9amer4eGtdfsexl7uDwPNpNRYoc1NvCbuuMugpfdPpdd342SucX6xASw\n0pDkFwPPw4pdJTc4QuP7b8Igaq3tlf0m3pp8K4x1KNszE0O672w/aydE4hr9cCZn\njh+Yrf/YHM2MZVAYhLZj8l42PMS+Ioqn7yZJRXODLrVFwUNsU20IF3BulsG+4Lez\nC/WxaXilAkhAs14vcs1chzTV\n=1Y/C\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/0fb5e167e8e332e3d40659406b3222a22747aa0e",
          "sha": "0fb5e167e8e332e3d40659406b3222a22747aa0e",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/0fb5e167e8e332e3d40659406b3222a22747aa0e"
        }
      ],
      "message": "multi_index: fix compilation failure with boost >= 1.91\n\nThis effectively reverts a3cb309e7c31853f272bffaa65fb6ab0a7cc4083 from PR #30194.\n\nThat PR reduced the multi_index type signatures as recommended upstream, but\nthis is no longer supported as of boost 1.91 because it is no longer necessary.\n1.91 drops support for the pre-c++11 work-arounds that bloated the type\nsignatures to begin with.\n\nThe upstream `BOOST_MULTI_INDEX_ENABLE_MPL_SUPPORT` define is meant to provide\ncompatibility with removed features, but it does not work for this case. Using\n`indexed_by` directly when defining the `multi_index` (as opposed to inheriting\nfrom it) works with all versions, and avoids the use of the back-compat define.\n\nThis is a slight regression when building against boost < 1.91 because the\nbloated type signatures are reintroduced in that case, but it's not significant\nenough to go to the trouble of introducing version detection and ifdefs.\n\nGithub-Pull: #35175\nRebased-From: 0bc9d354dfd8074d1c36a891a69b6585a8775c65",
      "committer": {
        "name": "fanquake",
        "email": "fanquake@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-30T14:06:17Z"
